
- implement Runnable use for create an object
- extend Thread use for separate and parallel thread
- Lifecycle : NEW -> RUNNABLE -> RUNNING -> TERMINATED.
 when thread is blocked by something , it will into NON-RUNNABLE state
 May be, it can into RUNNABLE again by the way of calling notify or notifyAll
- join(): the joined thread must run completely, then the original thread can run
- have 2 type of the thread: daemon Thread and normal thread.
 To thread become daemon thread, just set setDaemonThread(true)

- Deadlock is a situation in which two or many threads have to wait for each other forever.
  It is caused by accessing in synchronized method of an object that was locked from each other

